# Value iteration
def T_R_matrix(env, states, actions):
  T=np.zeros((actions, states, states))
  R=np.zeros((states, actions))

  for state in range(states):
    for action in range(actions):
      for i in range(len(env.P[state][action])):
        #print(env.P[state][action][i])
        prob, state_p, reward, done=env.P[state][action][i]
        T[action, state, state_p]=prob
        R[state, action]=reward
        T[action, state, :]=T[action, state, :]/np.sum(T[action, state,:])
  return T, R
In [39]:
# investigate discount factors
def VI_discount(t, r, discount_factors, max_iter):
  rewards=[]
  n_iters=[]
  time=[]
  policy=[]

  for gamma in discount_factors:
    exp=mdp.ValueIteration(t, r, gamma, max_iter=max_iter)
    results=exp.run()

    rewards.append(results[-1]['Reward'])
    n_iters.append(results[-1]['Iteration'])
    time.append(results[-1]['Time'])
    policy.append(exp.policy)

  return rewards, n_iters, time, policy

# plot discount factor analysis
def plt_discount(r, iter, time, algo, dataName):
  fig1=plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
  plt.plot(discount_factors, r, marker='o')
  plt.title('{} - Reward vs discount factor - {}'.format(algo, dataName))
  plt.xlabel('discount factor')
  plt.ylabel('Rewards')

  fig2=plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
  plt.plot(discount_factors, iter, marker='o')
  plt.title('{} - iterations to converge - {}'.format(algo, dataName))
  plt.xlabel('discount_factor')
  plt.ylabel('Iterations to converge')

  fig3=plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
  plt.plot(discount_factors, time, marker='o')
  plt.title('{} - Time vs discount factor - {}'.format(algo, dataName))
  plt.xlabel('discount factor')
  plt.ylabel('Time')

# plot data
def plt_analysis(data, algo, dataName):
  fig1=plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
  plt.plot(data['Reward'], marker='o')
  plt.title('{} - Reward - {}'.format(algo, dataName))
  plt.xlabel('Iterations')
  plt.ylabel('Rewards')

  fig2=plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
  plt.plot(data['Error'], marker='o')
  plt.title('{} - Error - {}'.format(algo, dataName))
  plt.xlabel('Iterations')
  plt.ylabel('Error')

  fig3=plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
  plt.plot(data['Time'], marker='o')
  plt.title('{} - Time - {}'.format(algo, dataName))
  plt.xlabel('Iterations')
  plt.ylabel('Time')

    n_iters.append(results[-1]['Iteration'])
    time.append(results[-1]['Time'])
    policy.append(exp.policy)

  return rewards, n_iters, time, policy

# compare VI and PI plot
def plt_compare(data1, data2, data3, data4):
  fig1=plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
  plt.plot(data1['Reward'], marker='o', label='VI-FL')
  plt.plot(data2['Reward'], marker='o', label='VI-FM')
  plt.plot(data3['Reward'], marker='o', label='PI-FL')
  plt.plot(data4['Reward'], marker='o', label='PI-FM')
  plt.legend()
  plt.title('VI-PI performance compare')
  plt.xlabel('Iterations')
  plt.ylabel('Rewards')

  fig2=plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
  plt.plot(data1['Time'], marker='o', label='VI-FL')
  plt.plot(data2['Time'], marker='o', label='VI-FM')
  plt.plot(data3['Time'], marker='o', label='PI-FL')
  plt.plot(data4['Time'], marker='o', label='PI-FM')
  plt.legend()
  plt.title('VI-PI Time compare')
  plt.xlabel('Iterations')
  plt.ylabel('Time')

Q-learning¶

In [ ]:
def Q_pruning(t, r, gamma, alphas, epsilon_decay, max_iter):
  rewards=[]
  n_iters=[]
  time=[]
  policy=[]
  inputs=[]

  for gamma in gamma:
    for alpha in alphas:
      for e in epsilon_decay:
        exp=mdp.QLearning(t, r, gamma, alpha=alpha, epsilon_decay=e, n_iter=max_iter)
        results=exp.run()
        #print(results)

        inputs.append((gamma, alpha, e))
        rewards.append(results[-1]['Max V'])
        n_iters.append(results[-1]['Iteration'])
        time.append(results[-1]['Time'])
        policy.append(exp.policy)

  return inputs, rewards, n_iters, time, policy

# compare q learning vs VI, PI
def compare_all(data1, data2, data3, dataName):
  fig1=plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
  plt.plot(data1['Reward'], marker='o', label='VI')
  plt.plot(data2['Reward'], marker='o', label='PI')
  plt.plot(data3['Max V'], label='QLeaning')
  plt.legend()
  plt.title('performance compare - {}'.format(dataName))
  plt.xlabel('Iterations')
  plt.ylabel('Rewards')

  fig2=plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
  plt.plot(data1['Time'], marker='o', label='VI')
  plt.plot(data2['Time'], marker='o', label='PI')
  plt.plot(data3['Time'],  label='QLeaning')
  plt.legend()
  plt.title('Time compare -{}'.format(dataName))
  plt.xlabel('Iterations')
  plt.ylabel('Time')
